### Framework01 CVE-2024-49721	A-354682735	
@code
android-12.0.0_r1/platform/frameworks/base/0005-InputMethodSubtypeArray-prevent-negative-count-injection.bulletin.patch
patch -p1 < 0005-InputMethodSubtypeArray-prevent-negative-count-injection.bulletin.patch
git add core/java/android/view/inputmethod/InputMethodSubtypeArray.java
git add core/tests/coretests/src/android/view/inputmethod/InputMethodSubtypeArrayTest.java

git commit -m "CVE-2024-49721
From ba59566c81e1e68476efb3479e5358dbb07c5a3c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adrian Roos <roosa@google.com>
Date: Fri, 2 Jun 2023 13:57:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] InputMethodSubtypeArray: prevent negative count injection

Fixes an issue where negative counts could be injected
via the Parcel constructor. The writeToParcel method
in that case would write data that a subsequent read would
not consume.

Fixes: 277916797
